President Obama congratulates India on its 63rd anniversary of independence. He praises India's non-violent struggle for freedom, rejection of terrorism, and belief in democracy, tolerance, and the rule of law. He highlights India's influence on the United States, including the debt owed to Mahatma Gandhi by leaders of the civil rights movement. The President emphasizes the strong ties between the Indian American community and both nations, and looks forward to his upcoming visit to India. He expresses a desire to further strengthen the strategic partnership between the two countries.